title: Frieze, 1875–1925
inscribed: Printed in top selvedge: "Stanford Wallpaper Co. 877"
description:
Alternating large and small foliate medallions with torches and spear, connected by waving foliate scrolls and foliate vining. Bottom has scrolls, waves, and floral motifs. Top has key pattern and floral motif. Background is a white and blue grid. Ground is a dark blue. Printed in blues, cream, gold micas, silver mica, and dark brown green.
Printed in top selvedge: "Stanford Wallpaper Co. 877"

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1875–1925.
1875–1925. Machine-printed on paper, mica, liquid. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-571.
